title: PXE, Inc - records request (Drug Enforcement Administration)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

I am requesting access to any and all records held by the Drug Enforcement Administration (DEA) relating “PXE, Inc,” a corporation registered in California, U.S.A also doing business under the names "Packers Express," and "Packers Express Export Logistics", conducting business at 21119 S. Wilmington Avenue, Long Beach, CA 90810. It operates in the freight-forwarding business / industry within the Transportation Services sector, related to its import and export of container shipments through the Ports of Long Beach, California and Los Angeles, California, primarily to-and-from the nation of Cambodia.

Specifically, I am requesting the following:
1.	Any DEA investigative reports, enforcement actions, intelligence bulletins, or case files concerning PXE, Inc; Packers Express and/or Packers Express Export Logistics from February 1996 to present, indicating suspicious and/or illegal activities under the laws of the United States or international treaties
2.	Any records relating to seizures, inspections, detentions, or investigations involving shipments or operations linked to PXE, Inc, Packers Express and/or Packers Express Export Logistics.
3.	Any communications or inter-agency reports referencing PXE, Inc, Packers Express and/or Packers Express Export Logistics.
4.	in connection with narcotics trafficking, controlled substances, precursor chemicals, or any other DEA-regulated concerns.
If any documents are withheld in whole or in part, please cite the specific exemptions under FOIA and release all reasonably segregable portions.

This information is requested journalistic purposes.
Thank you for your attention to this request. I look forward to your response within the 20 business days provided by statute.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Mary Patricia Nunan
